==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stopping-out
<hw>Stop"ping-out`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A method
adopted in etching, to keep the acid from those parts which are already
sufficiently corroded, by applying varnish or other covering matter with
a brush, but allowing the acid to act on the other parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stopple</ent>⟦br⟧
